1. Download Apache Maven
Open:
https://maven.apache.org/download.cgi
Download: apache-maven-3.9.x-bin.zip

2. Extract Maven
Extract to: C:\apache-maven-3.9.x
Folder structure includes: bin, boot, conf, lib, LICENSE, NOTICE

3. Set Environment Variables
Open: System Properties  Advanced  Environment Variables

Add M2_HOME:
Variable name: M2_HOME
Value: C:\apache-maven-
3.9.x

Add MAVEN_HOME:
Variable name: MAVEN_HOME
Value: C:\apache-maven-3.9.x

4. Add Maven to
PATH Add to PATH:
C:\apache-maven-3.9.x\bin

5. Verify
Installation Run in
CMD:

mvn -version

Expected output:
Apache Maven 3.9.x
Java version: 17.x

Troubleshooting:
If mvn not recognized:
- PATH incorrect
- Restart terminal
- Ensure mvn.cmd is present in bin folder
